socialMediaPlatforms.name: TikTok
socialMediaPlatforms.description: TikTok is a video-sharing social networking service owned by ByteDance, a Beijing-based internet technology company founded in 2012 by Zhang Yiming. It is used to create short dance, lip-sync, comedy, and talent videos.
socialMediaPlatforms.Impact: The paper mentions that the negative impacts of TikTok include a decrease in study intensity and exam scores, disruption of well-being, and indifference towards learning. The positive impacts include educational content and knowledge acquisition.

socialMediaPlatforms.name: Instagram
socialMediaPlatforms.description: Instagram is a photo and video-sharing social networking service owned by Meta Platforms. It allows users to share photos and videos, and also offers features like filters, stories, and direct messaging.
socialMediaPlatforms.Impact: Instagram users use this method to share their information and generate income, but it has some advantages and disadvantages.

socialMediaPlatforms.name: LinkedIn
socialMediaPlatforms.description: LinkedIn is a business and employment-oriented online service that operates via websites and mobile apps. It is mainly used for professional networking, including employers posting jobs and job seekers posting their CVs.
socialMediaPlatforms.Impact: Strengthen Business Networks. Sharing is the foundation of networking. ...

socialMediaPlatforms.name: Twitter
socialMediaPlatforms.description: Twitter is an American microblogging and social networking service on which users post and interact with messages known as 'tweets'. Tweets can be up to 280 characters long and can include links to relevant articles, websites, or other content.
socialMediaPlatforms.Impact: you can connect with people who share your interests in a particular field or subject.
